<div xmlns:perseus="http://www.perseus.org/meta/perseus.rdfs#" xmlns:dctype="http://purl.org/dc/dcmitype/" xmlns:tufts="http://www.tufts.edu/" xmlns:alph="http://alpheios.net/namespaces/tei" class="alpheios-lex-text_container en">
    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n5250" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κεράννῡμι, κεράω, κεραίω</span></b>  (cf.
          also <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κιρνάω</span> and <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κίρνημι</span>), aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κέρασσε</span>,
          part. fein. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κεράσᾱσα</span>, mid. pres. subj.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κέρωνται</span>, imp. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κεράασθε, κερᾶσθε</span>, ipf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κερόων-</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">το, κερῶντο</span>, aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κεράσσατο</span>, pass. perf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κεκρά̄ανται</span>, plup. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">-αντο</span>:
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">mix, prepare by mixing</span>, mid., for oneself,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">have mixed;</span> esp. of tempering wine with water, also
          of preparing water for a bath, <i><span class="en">Od.
            10.362</span></i>; of alloy, or similar work in metal, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χρῡσῷ δ᾽ ἐπὶ χείλεα κεκρά̄ανται</span>, ‘plated’
          with gold, <i><span class="en">Od. 4.132</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
    <div class="alpheios-lex-alph-source">From <u>
            <u>A Homeric Dictionary</u>
        </u> (Georg Autenrieth, New York, Harper and Brothers, 1891) </div>
</div>